Trauma History: The patient was attacked by a stalker in November 2009, which led to a diagnosis of PTSD in February 2011.
Medical and Psychiatric History: The patient has been diagnosed with PTSD and has been attending therapy since the incident.
Psychosocial History: The patient enjoys the arts and entertainment in Los Angeles, values family connections, and finds parenting challenging yet rewarding. They express pride in their children and acknowledge the difficulties of parenting.
Physiological Observations: The patient reports feeling run down and stressed, struggles with sleep, and experiences lethargy when not sleeping well.
Current Functional Status: The patient manages a doggy daycare, engages in artistic activities, and utilizes coping strategies learned in therapy to handle stress and emotions.
Progress Evaluation: The patient feels therapy has been tremendously helpful in managing their responsibilities and emotions, leading to a more rational approach to challenges.
Medications: The patient no longer uses medication and relies on proactive treatment strategies.
